3BIf%20Nebraska's%20Republican%20Governor%20and%20Republican-controlled%20Legislature%20were%20to%20change%20their%20electoral%20system%20this%20late%20in%20the%20cycle%20in%20order%20to%20unfairly%20award%20Donald%20Trump%20an%20additional%20electoral%20vote%2C%20I%20think%20the%20Maine%20Legislature%20would%20be%20compelled%20to%20act%20in%20order%20to%20restore%20fairness%20to%20our%20country's%20electoral%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20remarks%20come%20weeks%20after%20Trump%20touted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-nebraska-electoral-college-biden-2nd-district-omaha-explainer-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENebraska%20GOP%20Gov.%20Jim%20Pillen's%20support%20of%20a%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20change%20the%20state's%20system%20of%20allocating%20electoral%20votes%20from%20one%20determined%20by%20individual%20congressional%20districts%20to%20one%20that%20would%20award%20the%20state's%20five%20electoral%20votes%20to%20the%20statewide%20victor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20steadfast%20in%20my%20commitment%20to%20get%20winner-take-all%20over%20the%20finish%20line%2C%20thereby%20honoring%20our%20constitutional%20founding%2C%20unifying%20our%20state%20and%20ending%20the%20three-decade-old%20mistake%20of%20allocating%20Nebraska's%20electoral%20votes%20differently%20than%20all%20but%20one%20other%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTeamPillen%2Fstatus%2F1777882507544793455%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20governor%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENebraska%20Democrats%20vehemently%20fought%20back%20against%20this%20electoral%20change%20before%20the%20legislative%20session%20ended%20earlier%20this%20month%20and%20the%20measure%20didn't%20advance.%20Pillen%20floated%20a%20potential%20special%20session%20to%20complete%20%26quot%3Bother%20unfinished%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20would%20include%20the%20switch%20to%20a%20winner-take-all%20system.%20However%2C%20so%20far%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnebraskaexaminer.com%2F2024%2F04%2F04%2Fwindow-closing-on-backup-plans-for-winner-take-all-in-nebraska%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERepublicans%20lack%20the%2033%20votes%20needed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20the%20change%2C%20and%20the%20governor%20previously%20indicated%20that%20he%20wouldn't%20call%20a%20session%20unless%20he%20had%20the%20requisite%20support%20to%20get%20it%20through%20the%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Nebraska%20overwhelmingly%20backed%20Trump%20in%20the%20overall%20statewide%20vote%20in%20both%202016%20and%202020%20%E2%80%94%20part%20of%20a%20longstanding%20pattern%20for%20Republican%20presidential%20nominees%20%E2%80%94%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20was%20the%20victor%20in%20the%20Omaha-based%202nd%20Congressional%20District%20in%202020%20and%20thus%20secured%20its%20one%20electoral%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20other%20state%20in%20country%20that%20allocates%20its%20electoral%20votes%20by%20congressional%20district%20is%20Maine%2C%20where%20the%20political%20dynamic%20is%20flipped%3A%20Biden%20won%20the%20overall%20statewide%20vote%20by%20a%20wide%20margin%2C%20but%20Trump%20captured%20one%20electoral%20vote%20by%20carrying%20the%20state's%202nd%20Congressional%20District.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20change%20in%20election%20law%20in%20either%20state%20would%20immediately%20raise%20the%20stakes%20in%20what%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20a%20close%20November%20general%20election%20between%20Biden%20and%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbattleground-states-2024-presidential-election-road-white-house-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20scenario%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20Biden%20wins%20Michigan%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20and%20Wisconsin%20but%20loses%20Arizona%2C%20Georgia%2C%20Nevada%2C%20and%20North%20Carolina%20%E2%80%94%20granted%20that%20he%20also%20keeps%20every%20core%20Dem